  "text": "The TLS certificate validation implementation in envoyproxy/envoy is located under `source/common/tls/`. The abstract interface `CertValidator` is defined in `cert_validator/cert_validator.h` with pure virtual methods for cert chain verification. `DefaultCertValidator` (in `default_validator.{h,cc}`) implements X.509 chain verification via `doVerifyCertChain()` (calls `X509_verify_cert`) and `verifyCertificate()` for hash/SPKI/SAN checks. The `SanMatcher`/`StringSanMatcher` classes in `san_matcher.{h,cc}` handle Subject Alternative Name matching for DNS, URI, email, and IP types. `ContextImpl` in `context_impl.{h,cc}` is the base TLS context managing certificates and OCSP responses, with `ServerContextImpl` and `ClientContextImpl` as derived classes (the server context handles OCSP stapling). OCSP response parsing is in `ocsp/ocsp.{h,cc}` with ASN.1 utilities in `ocsp/asn1_utility.{h,cc}`. The `cert_validator/factory.{h,cc}` provides the factory for creating cert validators, and `cert_validator/utility.{h,cc}` has helper functions for certificate operations.",
